# Phase 3 â€” Business Questions

This phase focuses on answering real business questions using SQL.  
Each question below is directly supported by SQL queries written in this project.

---

## 1. What pizzas are available and how much do they cost?
To understand the menu offerings, I explored all pizzas along with their sizes and prices.

---

## 2. What are the pizza categories and ingredients?
This helps identify what types of pizzas are offered (e.g., vegetarian, non-vegetarian) and what goes into each pizza.

---

## 3. Which pizzas cost more than $15?
This question helps identify premium-priced pizzas on the menu.

---

## 4. What pizzas fall under the vegetarian category?
This analysis helps understand vegetarian options available for customers.

---

## 5. What is the most expensive pizza?
Finding the highest-priced pizza helps highlight premium products.

---

## 6. What are the details of each order along with pizza prices?
This links order details with pizza pricing to understand how much each order item contributes.

---

## 7. Which pizza was ordered and what category does it belong to?
This helps connect customer orders to pizza categories for category-level analysis.

---

## 8. On which dates were pizzas ordered and what pizzas were ordered?
This helps track ordering activity over time along with pizza names.

---

## 9. What is the total quantity of pizzas sold?
This gives an overall picture of total sales volume.

---

## 10. What is the total revenue generated from pizza sales?
This measures overall business performance in terms of revenue.

---

## 11. How many orders were placed on each day?
This helps analyze daily order trends and customer activity.

---

## 12. How much revenue did each pizza generate?
This identifies which individual pizzas are contributing the most to revenue.

---

## 13. How much revenue was generated by each pizza category?
This helps compare performance across different pizza categories.

---

## 14. Which pizza categories generated revenue greater than $30?
This filters out high-performing categories based on revenue thresholds.

---

## 15. Which pizzas were ordered more than once?
This helps identify popular or repeat-ordered pizzas.

---

## 16. How do pizzas rank based on total revenue?
Ranking pizzas by revenue highlights best-selling products.

---

## 17. How do daily orders accumulate over time?
Using a running total helps understand growth trends in orders over time.

---

## 18. Which pizza category is the top-selling by revenue?
This identifies the most profitable pizza category overall.
